rComments: I felt like I tried super hard and somehow just couldn't get full points in the labs (but oh well). However, Dr Forrest is super kind and will always explain things again if anyone has questions. I didn't do the best in the class but it's certainly the class that I valued and appreciated the most. I feel like I actually learned something

Best professor I've had throughout my undergrad. Really interesting course content, and super well explained. Labs are helpful and totally reasonable in terms of workload - once you get used to the style you will be able to finish the full lab + assignment within the class time. Super nice and encouraging, really makes you feel like going to class.

This class covers a lot of material and while there's a lot in terms of work load, if you ask questions and you participate, you do the assignments (labs) and you attend every class, you'll pass no problem. Jessica speaks fast but she's always there to answer questions and if she's open to feedback to improve her classes. She cares.

Articulate, conveys concepts well albeit sometimes a little too fast. Maybe it was just me but I struggled, but I never really liked ecology courses. Labs are straightforward, still fell asleep in class, the hardest thing for me was the group project/presentation which required using the scientific method on a data set which I've never done before.

One of the most logical and fair professors I've had. She's very attentive; she will never make you feel overwhelmed nor left out, unless you want her to. I usually zone out very easily during lectures and I've never done so during hers. The labs were fun. Study, ask questions if you're confused, and you can't fail.

Jessica is really friendly and has an awesome dry sense of humour. She was always very helpful without giving you the answers. This was the first class I took that actually gave me applicable knowledge for grad school and research. I REALLY enjoyed this class, the lectures and especially the labs were great!
